; Notes :{{note|imx6|i.MX6}}: mainline Linux has basic support ([[device tree]]s) for most i.MX6 boards<ref>{{cite web |url=https://git.kernel.org/cgit/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/tree/arch/arm/boot/dts |accessdate=2014-07-31 |title=mainlined ARM board device trees}}</ref> (including Nitrogen6x, Wandboard, RIoTboard), but board vendors may still recommend forked kernels for full functionality. Vivante GPU drivers are provided as userspace library BLOBs;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://boundarydevices.com/mx6-video-acceleration-raring-debian/ |title=i.MX6 Video acceleration on Ubuntu Raring (and Debian) |accessdate=2014-07-31 |date=2013-10-13}}</ref> a future open-source alternative might be [https://github.com/laanwj/etna_viv etnaviv] (Kosagi Novena).<ref name="OpenBSD61"/><ref name=etnaviv-coming>.{{cite web |url=https://www.crowdsupply.com/kosagi/novena-open-laptop/first-stretch-goal-complete |title=Novena - First Stretch Goal Complete! |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> :{{note|sitara|Sitara}}: Future [[Software development kit|SDKs]] for Sitara AM335x, AM4x, AM5x and Keystone SoCs will be based on a mainline kernel: "''The Sitara Linux SDK based on the 2014 LTS kernel is expected to be available from TI during the fourth quarter of 2014.''"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ti.com/lit/wp/spry259/spry259.pdf|title=ti-mainline-whitepaper|date=March 2014|accessdate=2014-09-09}}</ref>
